  "title": "Warehouse Assistant (Tuas) (Meals provided)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Perform warehouse operations including cargo handling, inventory management, and maintaining warehouse order to support efficient logistics and storage processes.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Load and unload cargos safely and efficiently to support timely warehouse operations</li><li>Place cargos and items accurately at designated warehouse locations to maintain organized storage</li><li>Conduct periodic stock taking and inventory checks to verify stock levels and identify discrepancies</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and orderliness of the warehouse to ensure a safe and efficient work environment</li><li>Collaborate with other stakeholders on warehousing matters to support smooth operations</li><li>Perform general housekeeping duties daily to uphold warehouse standards</li><li>Carry out other roles assigned by management to meet operational needs</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a valid forklift license to operate warehouse machinery safely</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to drive Reach Truck to enhance warehouse equipment handling capabilities</li><li>Experience in warehouse operations to contribute to efficient workflow</li><li>Demonstrate a positive attitude and willingness to learn for continuous improvement</li><li>Availability to start immediately to meet staffing needs</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work schedule: 5.5 days per week with breakfast and lunch provided.</li></ul>",
